properties.Name: StateLicensedCompany
properties.Description: An admitted or licensed company is a company that has been authorized by a particular state to sell insurance in that state.

Columns.Name: InsuranceCompanyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Customer.

Columns.Name: StateRegulatorId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a State Regulator.

Columns.Name: LicensedPeriodStartDate
Columns.Description: The starting date that the Insurance Company is licensed in the state.

Columns.Name: LicensedPeriodEndDate
Columns.Description: The ending date that the Insurance Company is licensed in the state.

Columns.Name: AdmittedDate
Columns.Description: The date that the insurance company was admitted to sell in the associated state.

Columns.Name: FirstSalesDate
Columns.Description: The first date that sales were made in the associated state or actual business practices were implemented.

Columns.Name: StateLicenseNumber
Columns.Description: The license number under which the Insurance Company does business in the associated state.

Columns.Name: LicenseApplicationDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Insurance Company applied for a state license.

Columns.Name: LicenseApprovalDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Insurance Company license was approved by the state.

Columns.Name: FirstBusinessOfferingDate
Columns.Description: The date that the Insurance Company first offered insurance products in the state.
